snippet.textDisplay:
Covid is primarily transmitted through respiratory droplets and contact routes...
One of the reasons that New Zealand was so successful in limiting Covid was the fact that they closed their borders completely fairly quickly and that the country is geographically isolated. As indeed are a lot of countries in the South Pacific.
The UK, being an island would have had a lot less fatalities if they had adopted the same measures and with the same speed as New Zealand. Unfortunately, politics overrode good science and common sense.
